<div1 type="letter" n="1928-10-11">
<head>Letter from Laura Armistead Carter to Wade Hampton Frost, October 11, 1928</head>
<pb n="1" id="fC0321011"/>
<opener>
Book, Bibliography<lb/>
Frost<lb/>
<dateline>
The Westmoreland,<lb/>
2122 California St., N.W.<lb/>
Washington, D.C.<lb/>
<date value="1928-10-11">October 11, 1928.</date>
</dateline><lb/>
<salute>Dear Jack:</salute>
</opener>
<p>Most of these enclosures are self-explanatory.</p>
<p>I would, however (1) call your attention to the statement, attri-<lb/>
buted to Fiske, <hi>re</hi> mortality in Lane's Pamlico colony 1585 (ii.82 MSS)<lb/>
We've done a lot of reading on the subject, beginning, of course, with<lb/>
different editions of Fiske's works and Father's notes thereon. The<lb/>
colony <hi>did</hi> have a hard time, but only &ldquo;foure&rdquo; died (see enclosed card for<lb/>
Thomas Herriot, for which Miss Brown deserves the credit).</p>
<p>(2): <hi>Re</hi> du Tertre, <add>(a)</add> I am sending you vol. i by to-day's mail as<lb/>
I understand from your letter that it contains practically everything that<lb/>
you thought you would need. (b) I think the enclosed cards, referring<lb/>
to du T. are now sufficiently straightened out to be a help instead of a<lb/>
hindrance, especially supplemented with the three verified pages of Father'<lb/>
MSS <add>also enclosed</add> dealting with the settlement of St. Christophe (1527) Guadeloupe and <lb/>
Martinique (1535). I did not rewrite the pages as the quotations are long<lb/>
and the needed corrections few: I would mention (iii.i.p.70) number of<lb/>
colonists and priests seems a bit involved (v.i. p. 75-du <unclear>T</unclear>) and<lb/>
(iii, i. p.90) last verbatim quotation this page not accurate: also last<lb/>
ref. (f. n.) to du T. this page should be v. i. p. <hi>80</hi> (not 89)</p>
<p>(3) Will make another attempt to get Melier's book for you this<lb/>
afternoon.</p>
<p>(4) Please thank Miss Fredericks for the clear copies (I. H. B.)<lb/>
of Father's MSS, also for the N. O. Med. &amp; Surg. Journals safely received.</p>
<p>(5) Will have Miss Brown rewrite card giving refs. to statements<lb/>
Busto y Blance in name of LeRoy de Mericourt. She can do it better than I.<lb/>
It is always good to hear from you, and very good to know that you were<lb/>
<pb n="2" id="fC0321012"/>
were<lb/>
-2-<lb/>
pleased with the last work we sent you. &ldquo;Praise from St. Quentin is<lb/>
praise indeede!&rdquo;</p>
<p>Hoping to have more material for you soon and with all manner of<lb/>
affectionate remembrances to you all.</p>
<closer>
<salute>Most truly and gratefully your friend,</salute>
<signed>Laura A. Carter</signed>
Dr. Wade H. Frost,<lb/>
School of Hygiene and Public Health<lb/>
615 North Wolfe Street,<lb/>
Baltimore, Maryland.<lb/>
Enclosures.<lb/>
</closer>
</div1>
</body>
